        <description>&lt;img src="https://regchien.info/p/macos-sets-the-third-party-input-method-as-the-default-input-method./1_OSsS9sormBmOU7drdMo85g.png" alt="Featured image of post macOS sets the third-party input method as the default input method." /&gt;&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Because I always use &lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://github.com/bs10081/rime-cx330&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;Rime-Cx330&lt;/a&gt; (support mixed English and Chinese input), but macOS will always set ABC as the default input method (arranged at the top), so when typing Chinese, you need to switch the input method to Rime first, which is still very troublesome.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://regchien.info/p/macos-sets-the-third-party-input-method-as-the-default-input-method./CleanShot_2022-03-24_at_17.32.20@2x_1648131669254_0.png&#34;
